{
  "_comment": "Wimba Video failover registry — mirrors image_registry.json. Each model maps an ordered cheapest-first provider chain; dispatch() tries chain[0] first and fails over. Prices are USD PER SECOND of output video (video bills per-second, unlike image's per-image). credits_for_video(model,seconds,size) multiplies by duration. Slugs are the EXACT provider API model ids (verified from ~/Claude/*-models.xlsx 2026-06-29); kie video slugs were NOT confidently verifiable so kie is omitted from chains here — chains use atlascloud/fal/aiml which have clean verified slugs, plus laozhang/vertex as the no-adapter legacy tail (caller falls back). DO NOT add a provider slug you have not verified — a wrong slug 404s and the provider is billed for nothing (image kie-slug lesson).",
  "_env": {
    "atlascloud": "ATLASCLOUD_API_KEY",
    "fal": "FAL_API_KEY",
    "aiml": "AIMLAPI_API_KEY",
    "kie": "KIE_API_KEY",
    "laozhang": "LAOZHANG_IMAGE_API_KEY (live LaoZhang account key, shared with the image path)",
    "vertex": "GCP_REFRESH_TOKEN (no adapter — caller legacy tail)"
  },
  "_features": [
    "text_to_video",
    "image_to_video",
    "reference_to_video",
    "video_edit"
  ],
  "_op_tool_features": [
    "reframe_video",
    "upscale_video",
    "lip_sync",
    "caption_video"
  ],
  "_price_unit": "usd_per_second",
